The paper deals with online scheduling for an energy harvesting communication system, which involves optimization of resource allocation and transmission policies. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of a finite-sized battery and energy harvesting process also suggests a possible connection to networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian sources and channels, which are commonly studied in multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the optimization of distortion in the transmission of source samples suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
